On “a cold chiny day ” indeed, Dec. 3, 1539, Abbat and brethren were turned adrift.² The treasures of the House, of course, were swept at once into the robber’s hoerd. The great costly work of King Genulph‚ of his piety, was ruthlessly pulled down and scattered. The very ashes of the Royal Founder and of the Royal Patron, his son and succsssor, Cenelm, Saint ' and Martyr, did not escape. Thus piteously vanished from the scene our “magnifical '' Mercian Monastery.
